He reminds us of the importance of checking for bats before performing maintenance on private property, as accidental destruction of one nest can lead to the death of up to 400 females and young, and possibly even the destruction of the entire local population.
Bats are protected by law, and it is illegal to destroy, harass or destroy their habitat.
Elizabeth Ferrell, the Scottish Bat Conservation Fund's chief executive officer, is calling on the public to help.
